{
  "texts": [
    "This controlled heating is crucial as it transforms the clay into MK, allowing it to react efficiently with calcium hydroxide (Ca(OH)₂) in cement paste to form Calcium Silicate Hydrate (C-S-H), the primary compound responsible for concrete strength [19].",
    "MK stands out for its higher initial reactivity compared to SF.",
    "Its faster pozzolanic reaction rates contribute more quickly to the development of concrete strength and durability.",
    "As a result, MK is especially valuable in high-performance concrete applications where early strength gain and increased durability are essential [3].",
    "POFAPOFA, a recycled material generated from burning palm oil shells and husks in mills, which is widely used in the construction industry."
  ]
}